<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="589" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,258,283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (including forewing): ♂, 
<quantity box="[741,880,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.9">5.9–6.2 mm</quantity>
. Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1066,258,283]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[1054,1066,259,283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) yellow to orange, marked with black stripes and patches. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[566,677,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with irregular black patch between ocelli, extending to ocelli. Frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation box="[329,399,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,399,331,355]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) with median longitudinal carina blackish ochreous, marking enlarged to a small rounded spot at apex, oblique lateral striations distinct. Lorum (
<figureCitation box="[787,857,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[842,857,367,391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) black at base. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1274,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) orange, with narrow black band along posterior margin. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[757,856,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with broad black stripe along claval suture and Mvein respectively, apex gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Aedeagal (
<figureCitation box="[320,386,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[372,386,475,499]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) ventral apophysis in lateral view approximately triangular, posterior margin slightly concave preapically. Style (
<figureCitation box="[359,426,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[411,426,511,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) apophysis in ventral view F-shaped. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[993,1061,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[1046,1061,511,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) stem in ventral view with lateral tooth at middle. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[530,612,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1415,203,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1420,190,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Angustuma basinigra sp. nov.: 1. male habitus, dorsal view; 2. male habitus, lateral view; 3. male head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. male face; 5. male pygofer, lateral view; 6. male pygofer side, lateral view; 7. aedeagal, lateral view; 8. aedeagal, ventral view; 9. connective and style, ventral view; 10. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
Fig. 
<number box="[583,612,547,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongate, expanded medially, macrosetae irregularly distributed, rows of elongate setae near interior submargin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
